"And neither can companies and organizations. In his Annual Report to the UK Parliament, the UK's Information Commissioner stated that Freedom of Information and Privacy (Data Protection) are similar, in that both are focused on good practice in handling information and both create important access rights to it. There is enlightened self interest. And data protection is not and should not be just for compliance sake – it should be because it is the right thing to do. Trust is essential to loyalty, prosperity and good government."
